name: kilojoule per hour
descripcion: Quotient from the 1000-fold of the derived SI unit joule divided by the unit hour.

name: kilojoule per day
descripcion: Quotient from the 1000-fold of the derived SI unit joule divided by the unit day.

name: nanoohm
descripcion: 0,000 000 001-fold of the derived SI unit ohm.

name: ohm circular-mil per foot
descripcion: Unit of resistivity.

name: kilohenry
descripcion: 1000-fold of the derived SI unit henry.

name: lumen per square foot
descripcion: Derived SI unit lumen divided by the power of the unit foot according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units by exponent 2.

name: phot
descripcion: CGS (Centimetre-Gram-Second system) unit of luminance, defined as lumen by square centimetre.

name: footcandle
descripcion: Non SI conform traditional unit, defined as density of light which impinges on a surface which has a distance of one foot from a light source, which shines with an intensity of an international candle.

name: candela per square inch
descripcion: SI base unit candela divided by the power of unit inch according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units by exponent 2.

name: footlambert
descripcion: Unit of the luminance according to the Anglo-American system of units, defined as emitted or reflected luminance of a lm/ft².

name: lambert
descripcion: CGS (Centimetre-Gram-Second system) unit of luminance, defined as the emitted or reflected luminance by one lumen per square centimetre.

name: stilb
descripcion: CGS (Centimetre-Gram-Second system) unit of luminance, defined as emitted or reflected luminance by one lumen per square centimetre.

name: candela per square foot
descripcion: Base unit SI candela divided by the power of the unit foot according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units by exponent 2.

name: kilocandela
descripcion: 1000-fold of the SI base unit candela.

name: millicandela
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the SI base unit candela.

name: Hefner-Kerze
descripcion: Obsolete, non-legal unit of the power in Germany relating to DIN 1301-3:1979: 1 HK = 0,903 cd.

name: international candle
descripcion: Obsolete, non-legal unit of the power in Germany relating to DIN 1301-3:1979: 1 HK = 1,019 cd.

name: British thermal unit (international table) per square foot
descripcion: Unit of the areal-related energy transmission according to the Imperial system of units.

name: British thermal unit (thermochemical) per square foot
descripcion: Unit of the areal-related energy transmission according to the Imperial system of units.

name: calorie (thermochemical) per square centimetre
descripcion: Unit of the areal-related energy transmission according to the Imperial system of units.

name: langley
descripcion: CGS (Centimetre-Gram-Second system) unit of the areal-related energy transmission (as a measure of the incident quantity of heat of solar radiation on the earth's surface).

name: decade (logarithmic)
descripcion: 1 Dec := log2 10 ˜ 3,32 according to the logarithm for frequency range between f1 and f2, when f2/f1 = 10.

name: pascal squared second
descripcion: Unit of the set as a product of the power of derived SI unit pascal with exponent 2 and the SI base unit second.

name: bel per metre
descripcion: Unit bel divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: pound mole
descripcion: Non SI-conforming unit of quantity of a substance relating that one pound mole of a chemical composition corresponds to the same number of pounds as the molecular weight of one molecule of this composition in atomic mass units.

name: pound mole per second
descripcion: Non SI-conforming unit of the power of the amount of substance non-SI compliant unit of the molar flux relating that a pound mole of a chemical composition the same number of pound corresponds like the molecular weight of a molecule of this composition in atomic mass units.

name: pound mole per minute
descripcion: Non SI-conforming unit of the power of the amount of substance non-SI compliant unit of the molar flux relating that a pound mole of a chemical composition the same number of pound corresponds like the molecular weight of a molecule of this composition in atomic mass units.

name: kilomole per kilogram
descripcion: 1000-fold of the SI base unit mol divided by the SI base unit kilogram.

name: pound mole per pound
descripcion: Non SI-conforming unit of the material molar flux divided by the avoirdupois pound for mass according to the avoirdupois unit system.

name: newton square metre per ampere
descripcion: Product of the derived SI unit newton and the power of SI base unit metre with exponent 2 divided by the SI base unit ampere.

name: five pack
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of five-packs (five-pack: set of five items packaged together).

name: weber metre
descripcion: Product of the derived SI unit weber and SI base unit metre.

name: mol per kilogram pascal
descripcion: SI base unit mol divided by the product of the SI base unit kilogram and the derived SI unit pascal.

name: mol per cubic metre pascal
descripcion: SI base unit mol divided by the product of the power from the SI base unit metre with exponent 3 and the derived SI unit pascal.

name: unit pole
descripcion: CGS (Centimetre-Gram-Second system) unit for magnetic flux of a magnetic pole (according to the interaction of identical poles of 1 dyn at a distance of a cm).

name: milligray per second
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the SI base unit second.

name: microgray per second
descripcion: 0,000 001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the SI base unit second.

name: nanogray per second
descripcion: 0,000 000 001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the SI base unit second.

name: gray per minute
descripcion: SI derived unit gray divided by the unit minute.

name: milligray per minute
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the unit minute.

name: microgray per minute
descripcion: 0,000 001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the unit minute.

name: nanogray per minute
descripcion: 0,000 000 001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the unit minute.

name: gray per hour
descripcion: SI derived unit gray divided by the unit hour.

name: milligray per hour
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the unit hour.

name: microgray per hour
descripcion: 0,000 001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the unit hour.

name: nanogray per hour
descripcion: 0,000 000 001-fold of the derived SI unit gray divided by the unit hour.

name: sievert per second
descripcion: Derived SI unit sievert divided by the SI base unit second.

name: millisievert per second
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the SI base unit second.

name: microsievert per second
descripcion: 0,000 001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the SI base unit second.

name: nanosievert per second
descripcion: 0,000 000 001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the SI base unit second.

name: rem per second
descripcion: Unit for the equivalent tin rate relating to DIN 1301-3:1979: 1 rem/s = 0,01 J/(kg·s) = 1 Sv/s.

name: sievert per hour
descripcion: Derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit hour.

name: millisievert per hour
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit hour.

name: microsievert per hour
descripcion: 0,000 001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit hour.

name: nanosievert per hour
descripcion: 0,000 000 001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit hour.

name: sievert per minute
descripcion: Derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit minute.

name: millisievert per minute
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit minute.

name: microsievert per minute
descripcion: 0,000 001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit minute.

name: nanosievert per minute
descripcion: 0,000 000 001-fold of the derived SI unit sievert divided by the unit minute.

name: reciprocal square inch
descripcion: Complement of the power of the unit inch according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units by exponent 2.

name: pascal square metre per kilogram
descripcion: Unit of the burst index as derived unit for pressure pascal related to the substance, represented as a quotient from the SI base unit kilogram divided by the power of the SI base unit metre by exponent 2.

name: millipascal per metre
descripcion: 0,001-fold of the derived SI unit pascal divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: kilopascal per metre
descripcion: 1000-fold of the derived SI unit pascal divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: hectopascal per metre
descripcion: 100-fold of the derived SI unit pascal divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: standard atmosphere per metre
descripcion: Outdated unit of the pressure divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: technical atmosphere per metre
descripcion: Obsolete and non-legal unit of the pressure which is generated by a 10 metre water column divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: torr per metre
descripcion: CGS (Centimetre-Gram-Second system) unit of the pressure divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: psi per inch
descripcion: Compound unit for pressure (pound-force according to the Anglo-American unit system divided by the power of the unit inch according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units with the exponent 2) divided by the unit inch according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units .

name: cubic metre per second square metre
descripcion: Unit of volume flow cubic meters by second related to the transmission surface in square metres.

name: rhe
descripcion: Non SI-conforming unit of fluidity of dynamic viscosity.

name: pound-force foot per inch
descripcion: Unit for length-related rotational moment according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units.

name: pound-force inch per inch
descripcion: Unit for length-related rotational moment according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units.

name: perm (0 ºC)
descripcion: Traditional unit for the ability of a material to allow the transition of the steam, defined at a temperature of 0 °C as steam transmittance, where the mass of one grain steam penetrates an area of one foot squared at a pressure from one inch mercury per hour.

name: perm (23 ºC)
descripcion: Traditional unit for the ability of a material to allow the transition of the steam, defined at a temperature of 23 °C as steam transmittance at which the mass of one grain of steam penetrates an area of one square foot at a pressure of one inch mercury per hour.

name: byte per second
descripcion: Unit byte divided by the SI base unit second.

name: kilobyte per second
descripcion: 1000-fold of the unit byte divided by the SI base unit second.

name: megabyte per second
descripcion: 1 000 000-fold of the unit byte divided by the SI base unit second.

name: reciprocal volt
descripcion: Reciprocal of the derived SI unit volt.

name: reciprocal radian
descripcion: Reciprocal of the unit radian.

name: pascal to the power sum of stoichiometric numbers
descripcion: Unit of the equilibrium constant on the basis of the pressure(ISO 80000-9:2009, 9-35.a).

name: mole per cubiv metre to the power sum of stoichiometric numbers
descripcion: Unit of the equilibrium constant on the basis of the concentration (ISO 80000-9:2009, 9-36.a).

name: pad
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of pads (pad: block of paper sheets fastened together at one end).

name: proof litre
descripcion: A unit of volume equal to one litre of proof spirits, or the alcohol equivalent thereof. Used for measuring the strength of distilled alcoholic liquors, expressed as a percentage of the alcohol content of a standard mixture at a specific temperature.

name: proof gallon
descripcion: A unit of volume equal to one gallon of proof spirits, or the alcohol equivalent thereof. Used for measuring the strength of distilled alcoholic liquors, expressed as a percentage of the alcohol content of a standard mixture at a specific temperature.

name: pitch
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of characters that fit in a horizontal inch.

name: degree Plato
descripcion: A unit of proportion defining the sugar content of a product, especially in relation to beer.

name: page per inch
descripcion: A unit of quantity defining the degree of thickness of a bound publication, expressed as the number of pages per inch of thickness.

name: pair
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of pairs (pair: item described by two's).

name: portion
descripcion: A quantity of allowance of food allotted to, or enough for, one person.

name: joule per tesla
descripcion: Unit of the magnetic dipole moment of the molecule as derived SI unit joule divided by the derived SI unit tesla.

name: erlang
descripcion: Unit of the market value according to the feature of a single feature as a statistical measurement of the existing utilization.

name: octet
descripcion: Synonym for byte: 1 octet = 8 bit = 1 byte.

name: octet per second
descripcion: Unit octet divided by the SI base unit second.

name: shannon
descripcion: Logarithmic unit for information equal to the content of decision of a sentence of two mutually exclusive events, expressed as a logarithm to base 2.

name: hartley
descripcion: Logarithmic unit for information equal to the content of decision of a sentence of ten mutually exclusive events, expressed as a logarithm to base 10.

name: natural unit of information
descripcion: Logarithmic unit for information equal to the content of decision of a sentence of ,718 281 828 459 mutually exclusive events, expressed as a logarithm to base Euler value e.

name: shannon per second
descripcion: Time related logarithmic unit for information equal to the content of decision of a sentence of two mutually exclusive events, expressed as a logarithm to base 2.

name: hartley per second
descripcion: Time related logarithmic unit for information equal to the content of decision of a sentence of ten mutually exclusive events, expressed as a logarithm to base 10.

name: natural unit of information per second
descripcion: Time related logarithmic unit for information equal to the content of decision of a sentence of 2,718 281 828 459 mutually exclusive events, expressed as a logarithm to base of the Euler value e.

name: second per kilogramm
descripcion: Unit of the Einstein transition probability for spontaneous or inducing emissions and absorption according to ISO 80000-7:2008, expressed as SI base unit second divided by the SI base unit kilogram.

name: watt square metre
descripcion: Unit of the first radiation constants c1 = 2·p·h·c0², the value of which is 3,741 771 18·10?¹6-fold   that of the comparative value of the product of the derived SI unit watt multiplied with the power of the SI base unit metre with the exponent 2.

name: second per radian cubic metre
descripcion: Unit of the density of states as an expression of angular frequency as complement of the product of hertz and radiant and the power of SI base unit metre by exponent 3 .

name: weber to the power minus one
descripcion: Complement of the derived SI unit weber as unit of the Josephson constant, which value is equal to the 384 597,891-fold of the reference value gigahertz divided by volt.

name: reciprocal inch
descripcion: Complement of the unit inch according to the Anglo-American and Imperial system of units.

name: dioptre
descripcion: Unit used at the statement of relative refractive indexes of optical systems as complement of the focal length with correspondence to: 1 dpt = 1/m.

name: one per one
descripcion: Value of the quotient from two physical units of the same kind as a numerator and denominator whereas the units are shortened mutually.

name: newton metre per metre
descripcion: Unit for length-related rotational moment as product of the derived SI unit newton and the SI base unit metre divided by the SI base unit metre.

name: kilogram per square metre pascal second
descripcion: Unit for the ability of a material to allow the transition of steam.

name: microgram per hectogram
descripcion: Microgram per hectogram.

name: pH (potential of Hydrogen)
descripcion: The activity of the (solvated) hydrogen ion (a logarithmic measure used to state the acidity or alkalinity of a chemical solution).

name: megawatts per minute
descripcion: A unit of power defining the total amount of bulk energy transferred or consumer per minute.

name: square metre per cubic metre
descripcion: A unit of the amount of surface area per unit volume of an object or collection of objects.

name: Standard cubic metre per day
descripcion: Standard cubic metre (temperature 15°C and pressure 101325 millibars ) per day

name: Standard cubic metre per hour
descripcion: Standard cubic metre (temperature 15°C and pressure 101325 millibars ) per hour

name: Normalized cubic metre per day
descripcion: Normalized cubic metre (temperature 0°C and pressure 101325 millibars ) per day

name: Normalized cubic metre per hour
descripcion: Normalized cubic metre (temperature 0°C and pressure 101325 millibars ) per hour

name: Joule per normalised cubic metre
descripcion: Joule per normalised cubic metre (temperature 0°C and pressure 101325 millibars).

name: Joule per standard cubic metre
descripcion: Joule per standard cubic metre (temperature 15°C and pressure 101325 millibars).

name: meal
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of meals (meal: an amount of food to be eaten on a single occasion).

name: page - facsimile
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of facsimile pages.

name: quarter (of a year)
descripcion: A unit of time defining the number of quarters (3 months).

name: page - hardcopy
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of hardcopy pages (hardcopy page: a page rendered as printed or written output on paper, film, or other permanent medium).

name: quire
descripcion: A unit of count for paper, expressed as the number of quires (quire: a number of paper sheets, typically 25).

name: quarter (UK)
descripcion: A traditional unit of weight equal to 1/4 hundredweight. In the United Kingdom, one quarter equals 28 pounds.

name: pica
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of picas. (pica: typographical length equal to 12 points or 4.22 mm (approx.)).

name: thousand cubic metre
descripcion: A unit of volume equal to one thousand cubic metres.

name: running or operating hour
descripcion: A unit of time defining the number of hours of operation.

name: ream
descripcion: A unit of count for paper, expressed as the number of reams (ream: a large quantity of paper sheets, typically 500).

name: room
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of rooms.

name: pound per ream
descripcion: A unit of mass for paper, expressed as pounds per ream. (ream: a large quantity of paper, typically 500 sheets).

name: revolutions per minute
descripcion: Refer ISO/TC12 SI Guide

name: revolutions per second
descripcion: Refer ISO/TC12 SI Guide

name: revenue ton mile
descripcion: A unit of information typically used for billing purposes, expressed as the number of revenue tons (revenue ton: either a metric ton or a cubic metres, whichever is the larger), moved over a distance of one mile.

name: square foot per second
descripcion: Synonym: foot squared per second

name: square metre per second
descripcion: Synonym: metre squared per second (square metres/second US)

name: half year (6 months)
descripcion: A unit of time defining the number of half years (6 months).

name: score
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of units in multiples of 20.

name: set
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of sets (set: a number of objects grouped together).

name: segment
descripcion: A unit of information equal to 64000 bytes.

name: Standard cubic metre
descripcion: Standard cubic metre (temperature 15°C and pressure 101325 millibars )

name: square
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of squares (square: rectangular shape).

name: square, roofing
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of squares of roofing materials, measured in multiples of 100 square feet.

name: strip
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of strips (strip: long narrow piece of an object).

name: stick
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of sticks (stick: slender and often cylindrical piece of a substance).

name: stick, cigarette
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of cigarettes in the smallest unit for stock-taking and/or duty computation.

name: standard litre
descripcion: A unit of volume defining the number of litres of a product at a temperature of 15 degrees Celsius, especially in relation to hydrocarbon oils.

name: ton (US) or short ton (UK/US)
descripcion: Synonym: net ton (2000 lb)

name: straw
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of straws (straw: a slender tube used for sucking up liquids).

name: skein
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of skeins (skein: a loosely-coiled bundle of yarn or thread).

name: shipment
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of shipments (shipment: an amount of goods shipped or transported).

name: syringe
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of syringes (syringe: a small device for pumping, spraying and/or injecting liquids through a small aperture).

name: telecommunication line in service
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of lines in service.

name: thousand piece
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of pieces in multiples of 1000 (piece: a single item, article or exemplar).

name: total acid number
descripcion: A unit of chemistry defining the amount of potassium hydroxide (KOH) in milligrams that is needed to neutralize the acids in one gram of oil. It is an important quality measurement of crude oil.

name: metric ton, including container
descripcion: A unit of mass defining the number of metric tons of a product, including its container.

name: metric ton, including inner packaging
descripcion: A unit of mass defining the number of metric tons of a product, including its inner packaging materials.

name: tonne kilometre
descripcion: A unit of information typically used for billing purposes, expressed as the number of tonnes (metric tons) moved over a distance of one kilometre.

name: kilogram of imported meat, less offal
descripcion: A unit of mass equal to one thousand grams of imported meat, disregarding less valuable by-products such as the entrails.

name: tonne (metric ton)
descripcion: Synonym: metric ton

name: ten pack
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of items in multiples of 10.

name: teeth per inch
descripcion: The number of teeth per inch.

name: ten pair
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of pairs in multiples of 10 (pair: item described by two's).

name: thousand cubic metre per day
descripcion: A unit of volume equal to one thousand cubic metres per day.

name: ten set
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of sets in multiples of 10 (set: a number of objects grouped together).

name: ten thousand sticks
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of sticks in multiples of 10000 (stick: slender and often cylindrical piece of a substance).

name: treatment
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of treatments (treatment: subjection to the action of a chemical, physical or biological agent).

name: tablet
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of tablets (tablet: a small flat or compressed solid object).

name: telecommunication line in service average
descripcion: A unit of count defining the average number of lines in service.

name: telecommunication port
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of network access ports.

name: percent volume
descripcion: A measure of concentration, typically expressed as the percentage volume of a solute in a solution.

name: wet kilo
descripcion: A unit of mass defining the number of kilograms of a product, including the water content of the product.

name: wet pound
descripcion: A unit of mass defining the number of pounds of a material, including the water content of the material.

name: cord
descripcion: A unit of volume used for measuring lumber. One board foot equals 1/12 of a cubic foot.

name: wet ton
descripcion: A unit of mass defining the number of tons of a material, including the water content of the material.

name: wine gallon
descripcion: A unit of volume equal to 231 cubic inches.

name: working month
descripcion: A unit of time defining the number of working months.

name: standard
descripcion:
A unit of volume of finished lumber equal to 165 cubic feet.
Synonym: standard cubic foot

name: Gunter's chain
descripcion: A unit of distance used or formerly used by British surveyors.

name: hanging container
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of hanging containers.

name: page
descripcion: A unit of count defining the number of pages.

name: mutually defined
descripcion: A unit of measure as agreed in common between two or more parties.
